Simulação de handshake TCP completo

Frame 1: 192.168.1.100:54321 → 93.184.216.34:80 [SYN]
  • Sequence Number: 1000
  • Window: 65535
  • Flags: SYN
  • Options: MSS 1460, SACK permitted

Frame 2: 93.184.216.34:80 → 192.168.1.100:54321 [SYN, ACK]
  • Sequence Number: 2000
  • Acknowledgment Number: 1001
  • Window: 8192
  • Flags: SYN, ACK
  • Options: MSS 1460

Frame 3: 192.168.1.100:54321 → 93.184.216.34:80 [ACK]
  • Sequence Number: 1001
  • Acknowledgment Number: 2001
  • Flags: ACK

Frame 4: 192.168.1.100:54321 → 93.184.216.34:80 [PSH, ACK]
  • Sequence Number: 1001
  • Acknowledgment Number: 2001
  • Flags: PSH, ACK
  • Data: "GET / HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: example.com\r\n\r\n"

Frame 5: 93.184.216.34:80 → 192.168.1.100:54321 [ACK]
  • Sequence Number: 2001
  • Acknowledgment Number: 1001 + len(data)
  • Flags: ACK

Frame 6: 93.184.216.34:80 → 192.168.1.100:54321 [PSH, ACK]
  • Data: HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n...

Frame 7: 192.168.1.100:54321 → 93.184.216.34:80 [FIN, ACK]
  • Flags: FIN, ACK

Frame 8: 93.184.216.34:80 → 192.168.1.100:54321 [ACK]
  • Flags: ACK

Frame 9: 93.184.216.34:80 → 192.168.1.100:54321 [FIN, ACK]
  • Flags: FIN, ACK

Frame 10: 192.168.1.100:54321 → 93.184.216.34:80 [ACK]
  • Flags: ACK
